      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>''One giant chunk of time devoted to counting votes may be gripping if you are a floor clerk in the House or Senate. But for 249 million other Americans, it's not as captivating.''</p>
        <p>ARI FLEISCHER, on plans to spread the state-by-state roll call over three nights at the Republican convention. [A21]</p>
      </block>
